A gas tanker exploded on Wednesday morning in Worcester in
the Western Cape. When the tanker exploded over four buildings caught fire however,
the driver of the truck survived without any injuries. The explosion happened near an Agri petrol station which led
to roads in the area have been closed. Worcester police spokesperson Captain Lindikhaya Mkhontwana told
News24 that the truck exploded as you enter town. “But we are not certain of the damage or whether anyone was
injured. Police and emergency services are on the scene to investigate,"
Mkhontwana said. Mkhontwana said at this stage it is difficult to say what
caused the explosion. “The area has been contained and the fire department is
trying to put out the flames. We can't get close to the incident yet because of
the blaze."  